ions: 50%\n- Appropriate use of inverse trig functions: 30%\n- Explanation of domain restrictions: 15%\n- Work shown with steps: 5%\n\n---\n\n### Week 5: Sequences and Series\n**Topics:** Arithmetic and geometric sequences, using formulas for nth term and sums.\n\n**Instructions:**\n- Understand definitions and differences between sequences and series.\n- Practice finding terms of arithmetic and geometric sequences.\n- Calculate sums for finite arithmetic and geometric series.\n- Apply formulas and word problems.\n\n**Tasks:**\n1. Identify sequence types.\n2. Calculate nth term and sum for sequences.\n3. Solve real-world application problems.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- Correct identification of sequences: 30%\n- Accuracy of nth term and sum calculations: 50%\n- Problem solving in application contexts: 15%\n- Clear presentation of solutions: 5%\n\n---\n\n### Week 6: Vectors in the Plane and Space\n**Topics:** Vector components, magnitude, direction, dot product, and cross product.\n\n**Instructions:**\n- Review how to write vectors in component form.\n- Calculate magnitude and direction.\n- Practice dot product computations.\n- Learn geometric interpretations and applications of dot and cross products.\n\n**Tasks:**\n1. Write vectors in component form.\n2. Calculate magnitude of vectors.\n3. Calculate dot products and interpret results.\n4. Compute cross products (space vectors) and find orthogonal vectors.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- Correct vector forms and calculations: 40%\n- Dot and cross product accuracy: 40%\n- Geometric interpretation explanation: 15%\n- Work process shown clearly: 5%\n\n---\n\n### Week 7: Matrices and Matrix Operations\n**Topics:** Matrix addition, multiplication, inverses, determinants, and applications.\n\n**Instructions:**\n- Practice basic matrix operations: addition, multiplication.\n- Learn how to find determinants and inverses of matrices.\n- Apply matrix concepts to solve systems of equations.\n- Complete examples and exercises.\n\n**Ta